Start with data wrangling

When data wrangling we will need a helper function for creating the quartiles for players. Additionally, it will be useful to exclude players that played less than 10 games or played less than 5 minutes a game. That is, we only want to include âqualifiedâ players.

Code 
# Returns quartile rank
quartile_rank <- function(x = 0:99) {
  # Set quartile
  quart_breaks <- c(
    -Inf,
    quantile(x,
      probs = c(.25, .5, .75),
      na.rm = TRUE
    ),
    Inf
  )
  cut(x = x, breaks = quart_breaks, labels = FALSE)
}
Solution
Code 
# Graphical data
nba_graph_dat <- nba_dat %>% 
  # filtering for qualified players
  filter(g >= 10, mp / g >= 5) %>% 
  # adding quantile ranks for each player
  mutate(
    ts_quant = quartile_rank(ts_perc),
    trb_quant = quartile_rank(trb_perc),
    dbpm_quant = quartile_rank(dbpm),
    ast_quant = quartile_rank(ast_perc),
    usg_quant = quartile_rank(usg_perc)
  ) %>% 
  # selecting only the relevant variables
  select(player, contains("_quant")) %>% 
  # making the data longer so it's tidy and we can use/graph it
  pivot_longer(
    cols = -player, 
    names_to = "variable", 
    values_to = "value"
    ) %>% 
  # arranging by alphabetical order of players
  arrange(player)

plot_df <- nba_graph_dat %>%
  filter(player == "Jamal Crawford")

Build the plot

Hints:

  • Image width is 8 in, height is 10 in â use code chunk yaml
  • center the image output â use code chunk yaml
  • shrink size down for display to 50% width â use code chunk yaml
  • All added text, except title, is done with annotate()
  • set axis.text to blank in theme
  • size 3 and 5 could be useful
Solution
Code 
ggplot(plot_df, aes(x = variable, y = value)) +
  geom_col(fill = "#F28291",
           width = 1) +
  geom_hline(aes(yintercept = y),
             data.frame(y = c(1:4)),
             linetype = "dotted") +
  scale_x_discrete(NULL,
                   limits = c(
                     "ts_quant",
                     "usg_quant",
                     "dbpm_quant",
                     "trb_quant",
                     "ast_quant"
                   )) +
  scale_y_continuous(NULL) +
  geom_segment(x = 0.5,
               y = 0,
               xend = 0.5,
               yend = 3) +
  geom_segment(x = 1.5,
               y = 0,
               xend = 1.5,
               yend = 4) +
  geom_segment(x = 2.5,
               y = 0,
               xend = 2.5,
               yend = 4) +
  geom_segment(x = 3.5,
               y = 0,
               xend = 3.5,
               yend = 1) +
  geom_segment(x = 4.5,
               y = 0,
               xend = 4.5,
               yend = 3) +
  theme(axis.text = element_blank()) +
  coord_polar() +
  annotate(
    geom = "text",
    x = rep(3, 4),
    y = 0.7:3.7,
    label = c("1st-25th", "26th-50th", "51st-75th", "76th-99th"),
    size = 3
  ) +
  labs(title = "Jamal Crawford",
       subtitle = "2014-15 Season") +
  annotate(
    geom = "text",
    label = c(
      "TRUE\nSHOOTING",
      "USAGE\nRATE",
      "DEFENSIVE\nBPM",
      "REBOUND\nRATE",
      "ASSIST\nRATE"
    ),
    x = 1:5,
    y = rep(5, 5),
    size = 5
  )
